# Leash Constitution

## Core Rules

1. Safety gates are non-negotiable. Every motor command passes through motor-limit, estop, and watchdog before reaching hardware.
2. Feature-gating is mandatory for hardware-specific adapters. The UGV adapter must not compile unless explicitly enabled (`--features ugv`).
3. The harness runtime is a library first. CLI and MCP server are thin shells around it.
4. External bridge clients depend on stable interfaces. Existing robot bridge APIs must not break without a compatibility shim.
5. Smoke tests gate every release. MCP, HTTP, and safety gate smoke tests must pass before any publish.
6. LLM agents operate through MCP only. No HTTP endpoint accepts unauthenticated commands.
